		<p>
			After spending my whole life in a small village in Bogor Regency, Indonesia, I decided to
			pursue my dreams: to leave the town, attend college, find a co-founder, then build a (or some)
			tech company(ies). Being a first-generation college graduate--first in my family to attend
			college--I was very lucky to find myself in a very supportive environment: I received a full
			scholarship from the Indonesian government to attend the Bandung Institute of Technology
			(ITB), majoring in Computer Science/Informatics. Something I'm really grateful for.
		</p>
		<p>
			I aspire to become an entrepreneur and make a positive impact with something I help create. In
			high school, I ran a clothing 'business' with my friends, and in college, started my 'career'
			as a freelancer programmer providing solutions for a university, telco company, oil & gas
			company, and SMEs. Basically writing code for most of my life.
		</p>
		<p>
			I am very competitive - that's why I joined many hackathons and competitions: gratefully won
			some, and lost more than I can count--such valuable learnings. All in all, I learned many
			things along the way and met amazing people.
		</p>
		<h1 class="title">What do I do?</h1>
		<p>I am a product builder at heart.</p>
		<p>
			Be it building solutions from well-defined problem statements the likes of in competitions,
			hackathons, and projects all the way to discovering problems and crafting solutions from the
			ground up with lots of uncertainty in startup settings.
		</p>

		<p>Here's a quote that best paints a picture of me:</p>

