		<p>
			My passion for building tech products, and aspiration to create long-lasting, impactful
			businesses have led me to build a startup called Neurafarm in my final year in college. I
			helped build a small team and the product from scratch as CTO, and later on focused on
			strategy, business, innovation, and making sure the company is well-funded, as part of my role
			as the CEO until 2022.
		</p>
		<p>
			My time there was amazing and full of challenges: deploying human-centric digital solutions to
			tens of thousands of smallholder farmers, and building an AI & data-enabled ecosystem to
			improve overall farmers' productivity, while marching many stakeholders to support our
			mission. We've manage to get support (and get funded) from Indonesia Ministry of Research,
			Singapore International Foundation, Global Green Growth Institute, Cisco, and many others. In
			2020, Neurafarm was featured in Temasek Review 2020.
		</p>

		<p>
			Now I continue to work on the same vision and mission at Elevarm to Elevate Farmers, as
			Co-Founder & CTO, where I lead teams of engineers and manage a portfolio of products that
			enable a data-driven agriculture ecosystem.
		</p>
		<p>
			I really enjoy working on complex strategic problems involving software engineering, design,
			and machine learning, especially in high-impact and multidimensional fields like agriculture
			and healthcare.
		</p>

		<p>I love to talk to people about product, technology, and how we can create social impacts.</p>

		<p>
			In my free time, I enjoy staying up to date with the latest advancements in technology,
			immersing myself in astrophysics, and experimenting with new ideas.
		</p>

		<p>
			To reach me, write to febiagil AT gmail.com. You can write to me in English or Bahasa
			Indonesia (preferred, if you know the language).
		</p>
